# Java Backend Conventions

## Package Structure

`org.dreamhorizon.pulseserver` → `resources/` (REST), `service/` (business), `dao/` (data), `dto/`, `model/`, `error/`, `module/`, `client/`, `util/`

## Service Layer

- Always define an **interface** and an **impl** in `service/<domain>/impl/`
- Return RxJava3 `Single<T>`, `Maybe<T>`, or `Completable` — never block
- Inject via Guice: `@RequiredArgsConstructor(onConstructor = @__({@Inject}))`

## DAO Layer

- SQL strings live in a `Queries` class (static constants)
- Use `MysqlClient` (writer/reader pools) or `ClickhouseQueryService`
- Name classes `*Dao`

## DTOs

- Lombok `@Data` on all DTOs
- Jackson `@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)` on response DTOs
- MapStruct mappers with `INSTANCE = Mappers.getMapper(...)` pattern

## Error Handling

- Use `ServiceError` enum (codes like `BE1001`) implementing `RestError`
- Throw via `ServiceError.X.getException()` or `getCustomException(message, cause)`
- Response shape: `Response<T>` with `data` and `Error.of(code, message)`

## REST Controllers

- JAX-RS annotations (`@Path`, `@GET`, `@POST`, etc.) from `vertx-rest`
- Use `RestResponse.jaxrsRestHandler()` to bridge RxJava to Vert.x
- Group by domain in `resources/` package

## Validation

- `ConstraintViolation` → 400 with `errors` array
- Validation logic in dedicated `ValidationModule`

## Code Style

- Google Checkstyle (140 char lines, 2-space indent)
- No wildcard imports
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
